108template <typename T, typename U>
109static inline ResourceErrorOr<CachedResourceHandle<T>> castCachedResourceTo(ResourceErrorOr<CachedResourceHandle<U>>&& cachedResource)
110{
111 if (cachedResource)
112 return CachedResourceHandle<T> { static_cast<T*>(cachedResource.value().get()) };
113 return makeUnexpected(cachedResource.error());
114}

116static CachedResourceHandle<CachedResource> createResource(CachedResource::Type type, CachedResourceRequest&& request, PAL::SessionID sessionID, const CookieJar* cookieJar, const Settings& settings)
117{
118 switch (type) {
119 case CachedResource::Type::ImageResource:
120 return new CachedImage(WTFMove(request), sessionID, cookieJar);
121 case CachedResource::Type::CSSStyleSheet:
122 return new CachedCSSStyleSheet(WTFMove(request), sessionID, cookieJar);
123 case CachedResource::Type::Script:
124 return new CachedScript(WTFMove(request), sessionID, cookieJar);
125 case CachedResource::Type::SVGDocumentResource:
126 return new CachedSVGDocument(WTFMove(request), sessionID, cookieJar, settings);
127 case CachedResource::Type::SVGFontResource:
128 return new CachedSVGFont(WTFMove(request), sessionID, cookieJar, settings);
129 case CachedResource::Type::FontResource:
130 return new CachedFont(WTFMove(request), sessionID, cookieJar);
131 case CachedResource::Type::Beacon:
132 case CachedResource::Type::Ping:
133 case CachedResource::Type::MediaResource:
134#if ENABLE(MODEL_ELEMENT)
135 case CachedResource::Type::ModelResource:
136#endif
137 case CachedResource::Type::RawResource:
138 case CachedResource::Type::Icon:
139 case CachedResource::Type::MainResource:
140 return new CachedRawResource(WTFMove(request), type, sessionID, cookieJar);
141#if ENABLE(XSLT)
142 case CachedResource::Type::XSLStyleSheet:
143 return new CachedXSLStyleSheet(WTFMove(request), sessionID, cookieJar);
144#endif
145 case CachedResource::Type::LinkPrefetch:
146 return new CachedResource(WTFMove(request), CachedResource::Type::LinkPrefetch, sessionID, cookieJar);
147 case CachedResource::Type::TextTrackResource:
148 return new CachedTextTrack(WTFMove(request), sessionID, cookieJar);
149#if ENABLE(APPLICATION_MANIFEST)
150 case CachedResource::Type::ApplicationManifest:
151 return new CachedApplicationManifest(WTFMove(request), sessionID, cookieJar);
152#endif
153 }
154 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
155 return nullptr;
156}

158static CachedResourceHandle<CachedResource> createResource(CachedResourceRequest&& request, CachedResource& resource)
159{
160 switch (resource.type()) {
161 case CachedResource::Type::ImageResource:
162 return new CachedImage(WTFMove(request), resource.sessionID(), resource.cookieJar());
163 case CachedResource::Type::CSSStyleSheet:
164 return new CachedCSSStyleSheet(WTFMove(request), resource.sessionID(), resource.cookieJar());
165 case CachedResource::Type::Script:
166 return new CachedScript(WTFMove(request), resource.sessionID(), resource.cookieJar());
167 case CachedResource::Type::SVGDocumentResource:
168 return new CachedSVGDocument(WTFMove(request), static_cast<CachedSVGDocument&>(resource));
169 case CachedResource::Type::SVGFontResource:
170 return new CachedSVGFont(WTFMove(request), static_cast<CachedSVGFont&>(resource));
171 case CachedResource::Type::FontResource:
172 return new CachedFont(WTFMove(request), resource.sessionID(), resource.cookieJar());
173 case CachedResource::Type::Beacon:
174 case CachedResource::Type::Ping:
175 case CachedResource::Type::MediaResource:
176 case CachedResource::Type::RawResource:
177 case CachedResource::Type::Icon:
178 case CachedResource::Type::MainResource:
179#if ENABLE(MODEL_ELEMENT)
180 case CachedResource::Type::ModelResource:
181#endif
182 return new CachedRawResource(WTFMove(request), resource.type(), resource.sessionID(), resource.cookieJar());
183#if ENABLE(XSLT)
184 case CachedResource::Type::XSLStyleSheet:
185 return new CachedXSLStyleSheet(WTFMove(request), resource.sessionID(), resource.cookieJar());
186#endif
187 case CachedResource::Type::LinkPrefetch:
188 return new CachedResource(WTFMove(request), CachedResource::Type::LinkPrefetch, resource.sessionID(), resource.cookieJar());
189 case CachedResource::Type::TextTrackResource:
190 return new CachedTextTrack(WTFMove(request), resource.sessionID(), resource.cookieJar());
191#if ENABLE(APPLICATION_MANIFEST)
192 case CachedResource::Type::ApplicationManifest:
193 return new CachedApplicationManifest(WTFMove(request), resource.sessionID(), resource.cookieJar());
194#endif
195 }
196 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
197 return nullptr;
198}

236ResourceErrorOr<CachedResourceHandle<CachedImage>> CachedResourceLoader::requestImage(CachedResourceRequest&& request, ImageLoading imageLoading)
237{
238 if (Frame* frame = this->frame()) {
239 if (frame->loader().pageDismissalEventBeingDispatched() != FrameLoader::PageDismissalType::None) {
240 if (Document* document = frame->document())
241 request.upgradeInsecureRequestIfNeeded(*document);
242 URL requestURL = request.resourceRequest().url();
243 if (requestURL.isValid() && canRequest(CachedResource::Type::ImageResource, requestURL, request.options(), ForPreload::No))
244 PingLoader::loadImage(*frame, requestURL);
245 return CachedResourceHandle<CachedImage> { };
246 }
247 }
248
249 if (imageLoading == ImageLoading::Immediate)
250 imageLoading = clientDefersImage(request.resourceRequest().url());
251 return castCachedResourceTo<CachedImage>(requestResource(CachedResource::Type::ImageResource, WTFMove(request), ForPreload::No, imageLoading));
252}

273CachedResourceHandle<CachedCSSStyleSheet> CachedResourceLoader::requestUserCSSStyleSheet(Page& page, CachedResourceRequest&& request)
274{
275 request.setDestinationIfNotSet(FetchOptions::Destination::Style);
276
277 ASSERT(document());
278 request.setDomainForCachePartition(*document());
279
280 auto& memoryCache = MemoryCache::singleton();
281 if (request.allowsCaching()) {
282 if (CachedResource* existing = memoryCache.resourceForRequest(request.resourceRequest(), page.sessionID())) {
283 if (is<CachedCSSStyleSheet>(*existing))
284 return downcast<CachedCSSStyleSheet>(existing);
285 memoryCache.remove(*existing);
286 }
287 }
288
289 request.removeFragmentIdentifierIfNeeded();
290
291 CachedResourceHandle<CachedCSSStyleSheet> userSheet = new CachedCSSStyleSheet(WTFMove(request), page.sessionID(), &page.cookieJar());
292
293 if (userSheet->allowsCaching())
294 memoryCache.add(*userSheet);
295
296 userSheet->load(*this);
297 return userSheet;
298}

384static MixedContentChecker::ContentType contentTypeFromResourceType(CachedResource::Type type)
385{
386 switch (type) {
387 // https://w3c.github.io/webappsec-mixed-content/#category-optionally-blockable
388 // Editor's Draft, 11 February 2016
389 // 3.1. Optionally-blockable Content
390 case CachedResource::Type::ImageResource:
391 case CachedResource::Type::MediaResource:
392#if ENABLE(MODEL_ELEMENT)
393 case CachedResource::Type::ModelResource:
394#endif
395 return MixedContentChecker::ContentType::ActiveCanWarn;
396
397 case CachedResource::Type::CSSStyleSheet:
398 case CachedResource::Type::Script:
399 case CachedResource::Type::FontResource:
400 return MixedContentChecker::ContentType::Active;
401
402 case CachedResource::Type::SVGFontResource:
403 return MixedContentChecker::ContentType::Active;
404
405 case CachedResource::Type::Beacon:
406 case CachedResource::Type::Ping:
407 case CachedResource::Type::RawResource:
408 case CachedResource::Type::Icon:
409 case CachedResource::Type::SVGDocumentResource:
410 return MixedContentChecker::ContentType::Active;
411#if ENABLE(XSLT)
412 case CachedResource::Type::XSLStyleSheet:
413 return MixedContentChecker::ContentType::Active;
414#endif
415
416 case CachedResource::Type::LinkPrefetch:
417 return MixedContentChecker::ContentType::Active;
418
419#if ENABLE(VIDEO)
420 case CachedResource::Type::TextTrackResource:
421 return MixedContentChecker::ContentType::Active;
422#endif
423#if ENABLE(APPLICATION_MANIFEST)
424 case CachedResource::Type::ApplicationManifest:
425 return MixedContentChecker::ContentType::Active;
426#endif
427 default:
428 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
429 return MixedContentChecker::ContentType::Active;
430 }
431}

433bool CachedResourceLoader::checkInsecureContent(CachedResource::Type type, const URL& url) const
434{
435 if (!canRequestInContentDispositionAttachmentSandbox(type, url))
436 return false;
437
438 switch (type) {
439 case CachedResource::Type::Script:
440#if ENABLE(XSLT)
441 case CachedResource::Type::XSLStyleSheet:
442#endif
443 case CachedResource::Type::SVGDocumentResource:
444 case CachedResource::Type::CSSStyleSheet:
445 // These resource can inject script into the current document (Script,
446 // XSL) or exfiltrate the content of the current document (CSS).
447 if (Frame* frame = this->frame()) {
448 if (!MixedContentChecker::canRunInsecureContent(*frame, m_document->securityOrigin(), url))
449 return false;
450 Frame& top = frame->tree().top();
451 if (&top != frame && !MixedContentChecker::canRunInsecureContent(top, top.document()->securityOrigin(), url))
452 return false;
453 }
454 break;
455#if ENABLE(VIDEO)
456 case CachedResource::Type::TextTrackResource:
457#endif
458#if ENABLE(MODEL_ELEMENT)
459 case CachedResource::Type::ModelResource:
460#endif
461 case CachedResource::Type::MediaResource:
462 case CachedResource::Type::RawResource:
463 case CachedResource::Type::Icon:
464 case CachedResource::Type::ImageResource:
465 case CachedResource::Type::SVGFontResource:
466 case CachedResource::Type::FontResource: {
467 // These resources can corrupt only the frame's pixels.
468 if (Frame* frame = this->frame()) {
469 if (!MixedContentChecker::canDisplayInsecureContent(*frame, m_document->securityOrigin(), contentTypeFromResourceType(type), url, MixedContentChecker::AlwaysDisplayInNonStrictMode::Yes))
470 return false;
471 Frame& topFrame = frame->tree().top();
472 if (!MixedContentChecker::canDisplayInsecureContent(topFrame, topFrame.document()->securityOrigin(), contentTypeFromResourceType(type), url))
473 return false;
474 }
475 break;
476 }
477 case CachedResource::Type::MainResource:
478 case CachedResource::Type::Beacon:
479 case CachedResource::Type::Ping:
480 case CachedResource::Type::LinkPrefetch:
481 // Prefetch cannot affect the current document.
482#if ENABLE(APPLICATION_MANIFEST)
483 case CachedResource::Type::ApplicationManifest:
484#endif
485 break;
486 }
487 return true;
488}

490bool CachedResourceLoader::allowedByContentSecurityPolicy(CachedResource::Type type, const URL& url, const ResourceLoaderOptions& options, ContentSecurityPolicy::RedirectResponseReceived redirectResponseReceived) const
491{
492 if (options.contentSecurityPolicyImposition == ContentSecurityPolicyImposition::SkipPolicyCheck)
493 return true;
494
495 ASSERT(m_document);
496 ASSERT(m_document->contentSecurityPolicy());
497
498 switch (type) {
499#if ENABLE(XSLT)
500 case CachedResource::Type::XSLStyleSheet:
501#endif
502 case CachedResource::Type::Script:
503 if (!m_document->contentSecurityPolicy()->allowScriptFromSource(url, redirectResponseReceived))
504 return false;
505 break;
506 case CachedResource::Type::CSSStyleSheet:
507 if (!m_document->contentSecurityPolicy()->allowStyleFromSource(url, redirectResponseReceived))
508 return false;
509 break;
510 case CachedResource::Type::SVGDocumentResource:
511 case CachedResource::Type::Icon:
512 case CachedResource::Type::ImageResource:
513 if (!m_document->contentSecurityPolicy()->allowImageFromSource(url, redirectResponseReceived))
514 return false;
515 break;
516 case CachedResource::Type::SVGFontResource:
517 case CachedResource::Type::FontResource:
518 if (!m_document->contentSecurityPolicy()->allowFontFromSource(url, redirectResponseReceived))
519 return false;
520 break;
521 case CachedResource::Type::MediaResource:
522#if ENABLE(VIDEO)
523 case CachedResource::Type::TextTrackResource:
524#endif
525 if (!m_document->contentSecurityPolicy()->allowMediaFromSource(url, redirectResponseReceived))
526 return false;
527 break;
528 case CachedResource::Type::Beacon:
529 case CachedResource::Type::Ping:
530 case CachedResource::Type::RawResource:
531#if ENABLE(MODEL_ELEMENT)
532 case CachedResource::Type::ModelResource:
533#endif
534 return true;
535#if ENABLE(APPLICATION_MANIFEST)
536 case CachedResource::Type::ApplicationManifest:
537 if (!m_document->contentSecurityPolicy()->allowManifestFromSource(url, redirectResponseReceived))
538 return false;
539 break;
540#endif
541 default:
542 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
543 }
544
545 return true;
546}

548static inline bool isSameOriginDataURL(const URL& url, const ResourceLoaderOptions& options)
549{
550 // FIXME: Remove same-origin data URL flag since it was removed from fetch spec (https://github.com/whatwg/fetch/issues/381).
551 return url.protocolIsData() && options.sameOriginDataURLFlag == SameOriginDataURLFlag::Set;
552}

554// Security checks defined in https://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#main-fetch step 2 and 4.
555bool CachedResourceLoader::canRequest(CachedResource::Type type, const URL& url, const ResourceLoaderOptions& options, ForPreload forPreload)
556{
557 if (document() && !document()->securityOrigin().canDisplay(url)) {
558 if (forPreload == ForPreload::No)
559 FrameLoader::reportLocalLoadFailed(frame(), url.stringCenterEllipsizedToLength());
560 LOG(ResourceLoading, "CachedResourceLoader::requestResource URL was not allowed by SecurityOrigin::canDisplay");
561 return false;
562 }
563
564 if (options.mode == FetchOptions::Mode::SameOrigin && !m_document->securityOrigin().canRequest(url) && !isSameOriginDataURL(url, options)) {
565 printAccessDeniedMessage(url);
566 return false;
567 }
568
569 if (options.mode == FetchOptions::Mode::NoCors && !m_document->securityOrigin().canRequest(url) && options.redirect != FetchOptions::Redirect::Follow && type != CachedResource::Type::Ping) {
570 ASSERT(type != CachedResource::Type::MainResource);
571 frame()->document()->addConsoleMessage(MessageSource::Security, MessageLevel::Error, "No-Cors mode requires follow redirect mode"_s);
572 return false;
573 }
574
575 if (!allowedByContentSecurityPolicy(type, url, options, ContentSecurityPolicy::RedirectResponseReceived::No))
576 return false;
577
578 // SVG Images have unique security rules that prevent all subresource requests except for data urls.
579 if (type != CachedResource::Type::MainResource && frame() && frame()->page()) {
580 if (frame()->page()->chrome().client().isSVGImageChromeClient() && !url.protocolIsData())
581 return false;
582 }
583
584 // Last of all, check for insecure content. We do this last so that when folks block insecure content with a CSP policy, they don't get a warning.
585 // They'll still get a warning in the console about CSP blocking the load.
586
587 // FIXME: Should we consider whether the request is for preload here?
588 if (!checkInsecureContent(type, url))
589 return false;
590
591 return true;
592}

594// FIXME: Should we find a way to know whether the redirection is for a preload request like we do for CachedResourceLoader::canRequest?
595bool CachedResourceLoader::canRequestAfterRedirection(CachedResource::Type type, const URL& url, const ResourceLoaderOptions& options) const
596{
597 if (document() && !document()->securityOrigin().canDisplay(url)) {
598 FrameLoader::reportLocalLoadFailed(frame(), url.stringCenterEllipsizedToLength());
599 LOG(ResourceLoading, "CachedResourceLoader::canRequestAfterRedirection URL was not allowed by SecurityOrigin::canDisplay");
600 CACHEDRESOURCELOADER_RELEASE_LOG("canRequestAfterRedirection: URL was not allowed by SecurityOrigin::canDisplay");
601 return false;
602 }
603
604 // FIXME: According to https://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#http-redirect-fetch, we should check that the URL is HTTP(s) except if in navigation mode.
605 // But we currently allow at least data URLs to be loaded.
606
607 if (options.mode == FetchOptions::Mode::SameOrigin && !m_document->securityOrigin().canRequest(url)) {
608 CACHEDRESOURCELOADER_RELEASE_LOG("canRequestAfterRedirection: URL was not allowed by SecurityOrigin::canRequest");
609 printAccessDeniedMessage(url);
610 return false;
611 }
612
613 if (!allowedByContentSecurityPolicy(type, url, options, ContentSecurityPolicy::RedirectResponseReceived::Yes)) {
614 CACHEDRESOURCELOADER_RELEASE_LOG("canRequestAfterRedirection: URL was not allowed by content policy");
615 return false;
616 }
617
618 // Last of all, check for insecure content. We do this last so that when folks block insecure content with a CSP policy, they don't get a warning.
619 // They'll still get a warning in the console about CSP blocking the load.
620 if (!checkInsecureContent(type, url)) {
621 CACHEDRESOURCELOADER_RELEASE_LOG("canRequestAfterRedirection: URL was not allowed because content is insecure");
622 return false;
623 }
624
625 return true;
626}
627
628bool CachedResourceLoader::updateRequestAfterRedirection(CachedResource::Type type, ResourceRequest& request, const ResourceLoaderOptions& options)
629{
630 ASSERT(m_documentLoader);
631 if (auto* document = m_documentLoader->cachedResourceLoader().document())
632 upgradeInsecureResourceRequestIfNeeded(request, *document);
633
634 // FIXME: We might want to align the checks done here with the ones done in CachedResourceLoader::requestResource, content extensions blocking in particular.
635
636 return canRequestAfterRedirection(type, request.url(), options);
637}
638
639bool CachedResourceLoader::canRequestInContentDispositionAttachmentSandbox(CachedResource::Type type, const URL& url) const
640{
641 Document* document;
642
643 // FIXME: Do we want to expand this to all resource types that the mixed content checker would consider active content?
644 switch (type) {
645 case CachedResource::Type::MainResource:
646 if (auto ownerElement = frame() ? frame()->ownerElement() : nullptr) {
647 document = &ownerElement->document();
648 break;
649 }
650 return true;
651 case CachedResource::Type::CSSStyleSheet:
652 document = m_document.get();
653 break;
654 default:
655 return true;
656 }
657
658 if (!document->shouldEnforceContentDispositionAttachmentSandbox() || document->securityOrigin().canRequest(url))
659 return true;
660
661 String message = "Unsafe attempt to load URL " + url.stringCenterEllipsizedToLength() + " from document with Content-Disposition: attachment at URL " + document->url().stringCenterEllipsizedToLength() + ".";
662 document->addConsoleMessage(MessageSource::Security, MessageLevel::Error, message);
663 return false;
664}

666bool CachedResourceLoader::shouldContinueAfterNotifyingLoadedFromMemoryCache(const CachedResourceRequest& request, CachedResource& resource, ResourceError& error)
667{
668 if (!frame() || resource.status() != CachedResource::Cached)
669 return true;
670
671 ResourceRequest newRequest = ResourceRequest(resource.url());
672 newRequest.setInitiatorIdentifier(request.resourceRequest().initiatorIdentifier());
673 if (auto inspectorInitiatorNodeIdentifier = request.resourceRequest().inspectorInitiatorNodeIdentifier())
674 newRequest.setInspectorInitiatorNodeIdentifier(*inspectorInitiatorNodeIdentifier);
675 if (request.resourceRequest().hiddenFromInspector())
676 newRequest.setHiddenFromInspector(true);
677 frame()->loader().loadedResourceFromMemoryCache(resource, newRequest, error);
678
679 // FIXME <http://webkit.org/b/113251>: If the delegate modifies the request's
680 // URL, it is no longer appropriate to use this CachedResource.
681 return !newRequest.isNull();
682}
683
684bool CachedResourceLoader::shouldUpdateCachedResourceWithCurrentRequest(const CachedResource& resource, const CachedResourceRequest& request)
685{
686 // WebKit is not supporting CORS for fonts (https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=86817), no need to update the resource before reusing it.
687 if (resource.type() == CachedResource::Type::FontResource)
688 return false;
689
690 if (resource.type() == CachedResource::Type::SVGFontResource)
691 return false;
692
693#if ENABLE(XSLT)
694 // Load is same-origin, we do not check for CORS.
695 if (resource.type() == CachedResource::Type::XSLStyleSheet)
696 return false;
697#endif
698
699 // FIXME: We should enable resource reuse for these resource types
700 switch (resource.type()) {
701 case CachedResource::Type::SVGDocumentResource:
702 return false;
703 case CachedResource::Type::MainResource:
704 return false;
705 case CachedResource::Type::LinkPrefetch:
706 return false;
707 default:
708 break;
709 }
710
711 if (resource.options().mode != request.options().mode || !serializedOriginsMatch(request.origin(), resource.origin()))
712 return true;
713
714 if (resource.options().redirect != request.options().redirect && resource.hasRedirections())
715 return true;
716
717 return false;
718}
719
720static inline bool isResourceSuitableForDirectReuse(const CachedResource& resource, const CachedResourceRequest& request)
721{
722 // FIXME: For being loaded requests, the response tainting may not be correctly computed if the fetch mode is not the same.
723 // Even if the fetch mode is the same, we are not sure that the resource can be reused (Vary: Origin header for instance).
724 // We should find a way to improve this.
725 if (resource.status() != CachedResource::Cached)
726 return false;
727
728 // If the cached resource has not followed redirections, it is incomplete and we should not use it.
729 // Let's make sure the memory cache has no such resource.
730 ASSERT(resource.response().type() != ResourceResponse::Type::Opaqueredirect);
731
732 // We could support redirect modes other than Follow in case of a redirected resource.
733 // This case is rare and is not worth optimizing currently.
734 if (request.options().redirect != FetchOptions::Redirect::Follow && resource.hasRedirections())
735 return false;
736
737 // FIXME: Implement reuse of cached raw resources.
738 if (resource.type() == CachedResource::Type::RawResource || resource.type() == CachedResource::Type::MediaResource)
739 return false;
740
741 if (resource.type() == CachedResource::Type::Beacon || resource.type() == CachedResource::Type::Ping)
742 return false;
743
744 return true;
745}
746
747CachedResourceHandle<CachedResource> CachedResourceLoader::updateCachedResourceWithCurrentRequest(const CachedResource& resource, CachedResourceRequest&& request, PAL::SessionID sessionID, const CookieJar& cookieJar, const Settings& settings)
748{
749 if (!isResourceSuitableForDirectReuse(resource, request)) {
750 request.setCachingPolicy(CachingPolicy::DisallowCaching);
751 return loadResource(resource.type(), sessionID, WTFMove(request), cookieJar, settings);
752 }
753
754 auto resourceHandle = createResource(resource.type(), WTFMove(request), sessionID, &cookieJar, settings);
755 resourceHandle->loadFrom(resource);
756 return resourceHandle;
757}

801 case CachedResource::Type::MainResource:
802 case CachedResource::Type::SVGDocumentResource:

804 case CachedResource::Type::ImageResource:

811 case CachedResource::Type::FontResource:
812 case CachedResource::Type::SVGFontResource:

854
855ResourceErrorOr<CachedResourceHandle<CachedResource>> CachedResourceLoader::requestResource(CachedResource::Type type, CachedResourceRequest&& request, ForPreload forPreload, ImageLoading imageLoading)
856{
857 URL url = request.resourceRequest().url();
858 if (!frame() || !frame()->page()) {
859 CACHEDRESOURCELOADER_RELEASE_LOG("requestResource: failed because no frame or page");
860 return makeUnexpected(ResourceError { errorDomainWebKitInternal, 0, url, "Invalid loader state"_s });
861 }
862
863 auto& frame = *this->frame();
864 if (!url.isValid()) {
865 CACHEDRESOURCELOADER_RELEASE_LOG_WITH_FRAME("requestResource: URL is invalid", frame);
866 return makeUnexpected(ResourceError { errorDomainWebKitInternal, 0, url, "URL is invalid"_s });
867 }
868
869 LOG(ResourceLoading, "CachedResourceLoader::requestResource '%.255s', charset '%s', priority=%d, forPreload=%u", url.stringCenterEllipsizedToLength().latin1().data(), request.charset().latin1().data(), request.priority() ? static_cast<int>(request.priority().value()) : -1, forPreload == ForPreload::Yes);
870
871 request.setDestinationIfNotSet(destinationForType(type));
872
873 // Entry point to https://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#main-fetch.
874 std::unique_ptr<ResourceRequest> originalRequest;
875 if (CachedResource::shouldUsePingLoad(type) || request.options().destination == FetchOptions::Destination::EmptyString) {
876 originalRequest = makeUnique<ResourceRequest>(request.resourceRequest());
877 originalRequest->clearHTTPReferrer();
878 originalRequest->clearHTTPOrigin();
879 }
880
881 prepareFetch(type, request);
882
883 if (request.options().destination == FetchOptions::Destination::Document) {
884 // FIXME: Identify HSTS cases and avoid adding the header. <https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=157885>
885 if (!url.protocolIs("https"))
886 request.resourceRequest().setHTTPHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::UpgradeInsecureRequests, "1"_s);
887 }
888
889 if (Document* document = this->document()) {
890 request.upgradeInsecureRequestIfNeeded(*document);
891 url = request.resourceRequest().url();
892 }
893
894 // We are passing url as well as request, as request url may contain a fragment identifier.
895 if (!canRequest(type, url, request.options(), forPreload)) {
896 CACHEDRESOURCELOADER_RELEASE_LOG_WITH_FRAME("requestResource: Not allowed to request resource", frame);
897 return makeUnexpected(ResourceError { errorDomainWebKitInternal, 0, url, "Not allowed to request resource"_s, ResourceError::Type::AccessControl });
898 }
899
900 if (!portAllowed(url)) {
901 if (forPreload == ForPreload::No)
902 FrameLoader::reportBlockedLoadFailed(frame, url);
903 CACHEDRESOURCELOADER_RELEASE_LOG_WITH_FRAME("CachedResourceLoader::requestResource URL has a blocked port", frame);
904 return makeUnexpected(frame.loader().blockedError(request.resourceRequest()));
905 }
906
907 request.updateReferrerPolicy(document() ? document()->referrerPolicy() : ReferrerPolicy::NoReferrerWhenDowngrade);
908
909 if (InspectorInstrumentation::willIntercept(&frame, request.resourceRequest()))
910 request.setCachingPolicy(CachingPolicy::DisallowCaching);
911
912 auto& page = *frame.page();
913
914#if ENABLE(CONTENT_EXTENSIONS)
915 if (m_documentLoader) {
916 const auto& resourceRequest = request.resourceRequest();
917 auto results = page.userContentProvider().processContentRuleListsForLoad(page, resourceRequest.url(), ContentExtensions::toResourceType(type, request.resourceRequest().requester()), *m_documentLoader);
918 bool blockedLoad = results.summary.blockedLoad;
919 bool madeHTTPS = results.summary.madeHTTPS;
920 request.applyResults(WTFMove(results), &page);
921 if (blockedLoad) {
922 CACHEDRESOURCELOADER_RELEASE_LOG_WITH_FRAME("requestResource: Resource blocked by content blocker", frame);
923 if (type == CachedResource::Type::MainResource) {
924 auto resource = createResource(type, WTFMove(request), page.sessionID(), &page.cookieJar(), page.settings());
925 ASSERT(resource);
926 resource->error(CachedResource::Status::LoadError);
927 resource->setResourceError(ResourceError(ContentExtensions::WebKitContentBlockerDomain, 0, resourceRequest.url(), WEB_UI_STRING("The URL was blocked by a content blocker", "WebKitErrorBlockedByContentBlocker description")));
928 return resource;
929 }
930 return makeUnexpected(ResourceError { errorDomainWebKitInternal, 0, url, "Resource blocked by content blocker"_s, ResourceError::Type::AccessControl });
931 }
932 if (madeHTTPS
933 && type == CachedResource::Type::MainResource
934 && m_documentLoader->isLoadingMainResource()) {
935 // This is to make sure the correct 'new' URL shows in the location bar.
936 m_documentLoader->frameLoader()->client().dispatchDidChangeProvisionalURL();
937 }
938 url = request.resourceRequest().url(); // The content extension could have changed it from http to https.
939 url = MemoryCache::removeFragmentIdentifierIfNeeded(url); // Might need to remove fragment identifier again.
940 }
941#endif
942
943 if (m_documentLoader && !m_documentLoader->customHeaderFields().isEmpty()) {
944 bool sameOriginRequest = false;
945 auto requestedOrigin = SecurityOrigin::create(url);
946 if (type == CachedResource::Type::MainResource) {
947 if (frame.isMainFrame())
948 sameOriginRequest = true;
949 else if (auto* topDocument = frame.mainFrame().document())
950 sameOriginRequest = topDocument->securityOrigin().isSameSchemeHostPort(requestedOrigin.get());
951 } else if (document()) {
952 sameOriginRequest = document()->topDocument().securityOrigin().isSameSchemeHostPort(requestedOrigin.get())
953 && document()->securityOrigin().isSameSchemeHostPort(requestedOrigin.get());
954 }
955 for (auto& fields : m_documentLoader->customHeaderFields()) {
956 if (sameOriginRequest || fields.thirdPartyDomainsMatch(url)) {
957 for (auto& field : fields.fields)
958 request.resourceRequest().setHTTPHeaderField(field.name(), field.value());
959 }
960 }
961 }
962
963 ResourceLoadTiming loadTiming;
964 loadTiming.markStartTime();
965 InitiatorContext initiatorContext = request.options().initiatorContext;
966
967 if (request.resourceRequest().url().protocolIsInHTTPFamily())
968 updateHTTPRequestHeaders(frame.loader(), type, request);
969
970 auto& memoryCache = MemoryCache::singleton();
971 if (request.allowsCaching() && memoryCache.disabled())
972 m_documentResources.remove(url.string());
973
974 // See if we can use an existing resource from the cache.
975 CachedResourceHandle<CachedResource> resource;
976 if (document())
977 request.setDomainForCachePartition(*document());
978
979 if (request.allowsCaching())
980 resource = memoryCache.resourceForRequest(request.resourceRequest(), page.sessionID());
981
982 if (resource && request.isLinkPreload() && !resource->isLinkPreload())
983 resource->setLinkPreload();
984
985 logMemoryCacheResourceRequest(&frame, DiagnosticLoggingKeys::memoryCacheUsageKey(), resource ? DiagnosticLoggingKeys::inMemoryCacheKey() : DiagnosticLoggingKeys::notInMemoryCacheKey());
986
987 auto& cookieJar = page.cookieJar();
988
989 RevalidationPolicy policy = determineRevalidationPolicy(type, request, resource.get(), forPreload, imageLoading);
990 switch (policy) {
991 case Reload:
992 memoryCache.remove(*resource);
993 FALLTHROUGH;
994 case Load:
995 if (resource) {
996 logMemoryCacheResourceRequest(&frame, DiagnosticLoggingKeys::memoryCacheEntryDecisionKey(), DiagnosticLoggingKeys::unusedKey());
997 memoryCache.remove(*resource);
998 }
999 resource = loadResource(type, page.sessionID(), WTFMove(request), cookieJar, page.settings());
1000 break;
1001 case Revalidate:
1002 if (resource)
1003 logMemoryCacheResourceRequest(&frame, DiagnosticLoggingKeys::memoryCacheEntryDecisionKey(), DiagnosticLoggingKeys::revalidatingKey());
1004 resource = revalidateResource(WTFMove(request), *resource);
1005 break;
1006 case Use:
1007 ASSERT(resource);
1008 if (request.options().mode == FetchOptions::Mode::NoCors) {
1009 if (auto error = validateCrossOriginResourcePolicy(*request.origin(), request.resourceRequest().url(), resource->response()))
1010 return makeUnexpected(WTFMove(*error));
1011
1012 if (auto error = validateRangeRequestedFlag(request.resourceRequest(), resource->response()))
1013 return makeUnexpected(WTFMove(*error));
1014 }
1015 if (shouldUpdateCachedResourceWithCurrentRequest(*resource, request)) {
1016 resource = updateCachedResourceWithCurrentRequest(*resource, WTFMove(request), page.sessionID(), cookieJar, page.settings());
1017 if (resource->status() != CachedResource::Status::Cached)
1018 policy = Load;
1019 } else {
1020 ResourceError error;
1021 if (!shouldContinueAfterNotifyingLoadedFromMemoryCache(request, *resource, error))
1022 return makeUnexpected(WTFMove(error));
1023 logMemoryCacheResourceRequest(&frame, DiagnosticLoggingKeys::memoryCacheEntryDecisionKey(), DiagnosticLoggingKeys::usedKey());
1024 loadTiming.markEndTime();
1025
1026 memoryCache.resourceAccessed(*resource);
1027
1028 if (document() && !resource->isLoading()) {
1029 auto resourceTiming = ResourceTiming::fromMemoryCache(url, request.initiatorName(), loadTiming, resource->response(), *request.origin());
1030 if (initiatorContext == InitiatorContext::Worker) {
1031 ASSERT(is<CachedRawResource>(resource.get()));
1032 downcast<CachedRawResource>(resource.get())->finishedTimingForWorkerLoad(WTFMove(resourceTiming));
1033 } else {
1034 ASSERT(initiatorContext == InitiatorContext::Document);
1035 m_resourceTimingInfo.storeResourceTimingInitiatorInformation(resource, request.initiatorName(), &frame);
1036 m_resourceTimingInfo.addResourceTiming(*resource.get(), *document(), WTFMove(resourceTiming));
1037 }
1038 }
1039
1040 if (forPreload == ForPreload::No)
1041 resource->setLoadPriority(request.priority());
1042 }
1043 break;
1044 }
1045 ASSERT(resource);
1046 resource->setOriginalRequest(WTFMove(originalRequest));
1047
1048 if (forPreload == ForPreload::No && resource->loader() && resource->ignoreForRequestCount()) {
1049 resource->setIgnoreForRequestCount(false);
1050 incrementRequestCount(*resource);
1051 }
1052
1053 if ((policy != Use || resource->stillNeedsLoad()) && imageLoading == ImageLoading::Immediate) {
1054 resource->load(*this);
1055
1056 // We don't support immediate loads, but we do support immediate failure.
1057 if (resource->errorOccurred()) {
1058 if (resource->allowsCaching() && resource->inCache())
1059 memoryCache.remove(*resource);
1060
1061 auto resourceError = resource->resourceError();
1062 // Synchronous cancellations are likely due to access control.
1063 if (resourceError.isNull() || resourceError.isCancellation())
1064 return makeUnexpected(ResourceError { String(), 0, url, String(), ResourceError::Type::AccessControl });
1065 return makeUnexpected(resourceError);
1066 }
1067 }
1068
1069 if (document() && !document()->loadEventFinished() && !resource->resourceRequest().url().protocolIsData())
1070 m_validatedURLs.add(resource->resourceRequest().url().string());
1071
1072 ASSERT(resource->url() == url.string());
1073 m_documentResources.set(resource->url().string(), resource);
1074#if ENABLE(RESOURCE_LOAD_STATISTICS)
1075 frame.loader().client().didLoadFromRegistrableDomain(RegistrableDomain(resource->resourceRequest().url()));
1076#endif
1077 return resource;
1078}

1095CachedResourceHandle<CachedResource> CachedResourceLoader::revalidateResource(CachedResourceRequest&& request, CachedResource& resource)
1096{
1097 ASSERT(resource.inCache());
1098 auto& memoryCache = MemoryCache::singleton();
1099 ASSERT(!memoryCache.disabled());
1100 ASSERT(resource.canUseCacheValidator());
1101 ASSERT(!resource.resourceToRevalidate());
1102 ASSERT(resource.allowsCaching());
1103
1104 auto newResource = createResource(WTFMove(request), resource);
1105
1106 LOG(ResourceLoading, "Resource %p created to revalidate %p", newResource.get(), &resource);
1107 newResource->setResourceToRevalidate(&resource);
1108
1109 memoryCache.remove(resource);
1110 memoryCache.add(*newResource);
1111
1112 m_resourceTimingInfo.storeResourceTimingInitiatorInformation(newResource, newResource->initiatorName(), frame());
1113
1114 return newResource;
1115}

1117CachedResourceHandle<CachedResource> CachedResourceLoader::loadResource(CachedResource::Type type, PAL::SessionID sessionID, CachedResourceRequest&& request, const CookieJar& cookieJar, const Settings& settings)
1118{
1119 auto& memoryCache = MemoryCache::singleton();
1120 ASSERT(!request.allowsCaching() || !memoryCache.resourceForRequest(request.resourceRequest(), sessionID)
1121 || request.resourceRequest().cachePolicy() == ResourceRequestCachePolicy::DoNotUseAnyCache || request.resourceRequest().cachePolicy() == ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReloadIgnoringCacheData || request.resourceRequest().cachePolicy() == ResourceRequestCachePolicy::RefreshAnyCacheData);
1122
1123 LOG(ResourceLoading, "Loading CachedResource for '%s'.", request.resourceRequest().url().stringCenterEllipsizedToLength().latin1().data());
1124
1125 auto resource = createResource(type, WTFMove(request), sessionID, &cookieJar, settings);
1126
1127 if (resource->allowsCaching())
1128 memoryCache.add(*resource);
1129
1130 m_resourceTimingInfo.storeResourceTimingInitiatorInformation(resource, resource->initiatorName(), frame());
1131
1132 return resource;
1133}

1140static void logResourceRevalidationDecision(CachedResource::RevalidationDecision reason, const Frame* frame)
1141{
1142 if (!frame || !frame->page())
1143 return;
1144 auto& logClient = frame->page()->diagnosticLoggingClient();
1145 switch (reason) {
1146 case CachedResource::RevalidationDecision::No:
1147 break;
1148 case CachedResource::RevalidationDecision::YesDueToExpired:
1149 logRevalidation(DiagnosticLoggingKeys::isExpiredKey(), logClient);
1150 break;
1151 case CachedResource::RevalidationDecision::YesDueToNoStore:
1152 logRevalidation(DiagnosticLoggingKeys::noStoreKey(), logClient);
1153 break;
1154 case CachedResource::RevalidationDecision::YesDueToNoCache:
1155 logRevalidation(DiagnosticLoggingKeys::noCacheKey(), logClient);
1156 break;
1157 case CachedResource::RevalidationDecision::YesDueToCachePolicy:
1158 logRevalidation(DiagnosticLoggingKeys::reloadKey(), logClient);
1159 break;
1160 }

1162
1163CachedResourceLoader::RevalidationPolicy CachedResourceLoader::determineRevalidationPolicy(CachedResource::Type type, CachedResourceRequest& cachedResourceRequest, CachedResource* existingResource, ForPreload forPreload, ImageLoading imageLoading) const
1164{
1165 auto& request = cachedResourceRequest.resourceRequest();
1166
1167 if (!existingResource)
1168 return Load;
1169
1170 if (request.cachePolicy() == ResourceRequestCachePolicy::DoNotUseAnyCache || request.cachePolicy() == ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReloadIgnoringCacheData)
1171 return Load;
1172
1173 if (request.cachePolicy() == ResourceRequestCachePolicy::RefreshAnyCacheData)
1174 return Reload;
1175
1176#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
1177 // FIXME: We should validate/specify this behavior.
1178 if (cachedResourceRequest.options().serviceWorkerRegistrationIdentifier != existingResource->options().serviceWorkerRegistrationIdentifier) {
1179 LOG(ResourceLoading, "CachedResourceLoader::determineRevalidationPolicy reloading because selected service worker differs");
1180 return Reload;
1181 }
1182#endif
1183
1184 // We already have a preload going for this URL.
1185 if (forPreload == ForPreload::Yes && existingResource->isPreloaded())
1186 return Use;
1187
1188 // If the same URL has been loaded as a different type, we need to reload.
1189 if (existingResource->type() != type) {
1190 LOG(ResourceLoading, "CachedResourceLoader::determineRevalidationPolicy reloading due to type mismatch.");
1191 logMemoryCacheResourceRequest(frame(), DiagnosticLoggingKeys::inMemoryCacheKey(), DiagnosticLoggingKeys::unusedReasonTypeMismatchKey());
1192 return Reload;
1193 }
1194
1195 if (!existingResource->varyHeaderValuesMatch(request))
1196 return Reload;
1197
1198 auto* textDecoder = existingResource->textResourceDecoder();
1199 if (textDecoder && !textDecoder->hasEqualEncodingForCharset(cachedResourceRequest.charset())) {
1200 if (!existingResource->hasUnknownEncoding())
1201 return Reload;
1202 existingResource->setHasUnknownEncoding(false);
1203 existingResource->setEncoding(cachedResourceRequest.charset());
1204 }
1205
1206 // FIXME: We should use the same cache policy for all resource types. The raw resource policy is overly strict
1207 // while the normal subresource policy is too loose.
1208 if (existingResource->isMainOrMediaOrIconOrRawResource() && frame()) {
1209 bool strictPolicyDisabled = frame()->loader().isStrictRawResourceValidationPolicyDisabledForTesting();
1210 bool canReuseRawResource = strictPolicyDisabled || downcast<CachedRawResource>(*existingResource).canReuse(request);
1211 if (!canReuseRawResource)
1212 return Reload;
1213 }
1214
1215 // Conditional requests should have failed canReuse check.
1216 ASSERT(!request.isConditional());
1217
1218 // Do not load from cache if images are not enabled. The load for this image will be blocked in CachedImage::load.
1219 if (imageLoading == ImageLoading::DeferredUntilVisible)
1220 return Reload;
1221
1222 // Don't reload resources while pasting or if cache mode allows stale resources.
1223 if (m_allowStaleResources || cachedResourceRequest.options().cache == FetchOptions::Cache::ForceCache || cachedResourceRequest.options().cache == FetchOptions::Cache::OnlyIfCached)
1224 return Use;
1225
1226 ASSERT(cachedResourceRequest.options().cache == FetchOptions::Cache::Default || cachedResourceRequest.options().cache == FetchOptions::Cache::NoCache);
1227
1228 // Always use preloads.
1229 if (existingResource->isPreloaded())
1230 return Use;
1231
1232 // We can find resources that are being validated from cache only when validation is just successfully completing.
1233 if (existingResource->validationCompleting())
1234 return Use;
1235 ASSERT(!existingResource->validationInProgress());
1236
1237 if (is<CachedImage>(*existingResource) && downcast<CachedImage>(*existingResource).canSkipRevalidation(*this, cachedResourceRequest))
1238 return Use;
1239
1240 auto cachePolicy = this->cachePolicy(type, request.url());
1241
1242 // Validate the redirect chain.
1243 bool cachePolicyIsHistoryBuffer = cachePolicy == CachePolicy::HistoryBuffer;
1244 if (!existingResource->redirectChainAllowsReuse(cachePolicyIsHistoryBuffer ? ReuseExpiredRedirection : DoNotReuseExpiredRedirection)) {
1245 LOG(ResourceLoading, "CachedResourceLoader::determineRevalidationPolicy reloading due to not cached or expired redirections.");
1246 logMemoryCacheResourceRequest(frame(), DiagnosticLoggingKeys::inMemoryCacheKey(), DiagnosticLoggingKeys::unusedReasonRedirectChainKey());
1247 return Reload;
1248 }
1249
1250 // CachePolicy::HistoryBuffer uses the cache except if this is a main resource with "cache-control: no-store".
1251 if (cachePolicyIsHistoryBuffer) {
1252 // FIXME: Ignoring "cache-control: no-cache" for sub-resources on history navigation but not the main
1253 // resource is inconsistent. We should probably harmonize this.
1254 if (!existingResource->response().cacheControlContainsNoStore() || type != CachedResource::Type::MainResource)
1255 return Use;
1256 }
1257
1258 // Don't reuse resources with Cache-control: no-store.
1259 if (existingResource->response().cacheControlContainsNoStore()) {
1260 LOG(ResourceLoading, "CachedResourceLoader::determineRevalidationPolicy reloading due to Cache-control: no-store.");
1261 logMemoryCacheResourceRequest(frame(), DiagnosticLoggingKeys::inMemoryCacheKey(), DiagnosticLoggingKeys::unusedReasonNoStoreKey());
1262 return Reload;
1263 }
1264
1265 // If credentials were sent with the previous request and won't be
1266 // with this one, or vice versa, re-fetch the resource.
1267 //
1268 // This helps with the case where the server sends back
1269 // "Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *" all the time, but some of the
1270 // client's requests are made without CORS and some with.
1271 if (existingResource->resourceRequest().allowCookies() != request.allowCookies() || existingResource->options().credentials != cachedResourceRequest.options().credentials) {
1272 LOG(ResourceLoading, "CachedResourceLoader::determineRevalidationPolicy reloading due to difference in credentials settings.");
1273 logMemoryCacheResourceRequest(frame(), DiagnosticLoggingKeys::inMemoryCacheKey(), DiagnosticLoggingKeys::unusedReasonCredentialSettingsKey());
1274 return Reload;
1275 }
1276
1277 // During the initial load, avoid loading the same resource multiple times for a single document, even if the cache policies would tell us to.
1278 if (document() && !document()->loadEventFinished() && m_validatedURLs.contains(existingResource->url().string()))
1279 return Use;
1280
1281 // CachePolicy::Reload always reloads
1282 if (cachePolicy == CachePolicy::Reload) {
1283 LOG(ResourceLoading, "CachedResourceLoader::determineRevalidationPolicy reloading due to CachePolicyReload.");
1284 logMemoryCacheResourceRequest(frame(), DiagnosticLoggingKeys::inMemoryCacheKey(), DiagnosticLoggingKeys::unusedReasonReloadKey());
1285 return Reload;
1286 }
1287
1288 // We'll try to reload the resource if it failed last time.
1289 if (existingResource->errorOccurred()) {
1290 LOG(ResourceLoading, "CachedResourceLoader::determineRevalidationPolicye reloading due to resource being in the error state");
1291 logMemoryCacheResourceRequest(frame(), DiagnosticLoggingKeys::inMemoryCacheKey(), DiagnosticLoggingKeys::unusedReasonErrorKey());
1292 return Reload;
1293 }
1294
1295 if (existingResource->isLoading()) {
1296 // Do not use cached main resources that are still loading because sharing
1297 // loading CachedResources in this case causes issues with regards to cancellation.
1298 // If one of the DocumentLoader clients decides to cancel the load, then the load
1299 // would be cancelled for all other DocumentLoaders as well.
1300 if (type == CachedResource::Type::MainResource)
1301 return Reload;
1302 // For cached subresources that are still loading we ignore the cache policy.
1303 return Use;
1304 }
1305
1306 auto revalidationDecision = existingResource->makeRevalidationDecision(cachePolicy);
1307 logResourceRevalidationDecision(revalidationDecision, frame());
1308
1309 // Check if the cache headers requires us to revalidate (cache expiration for example).
1310 if (revalidationDecision != CachedResource::RevalidationDecision::No) {
1311 // See if the resource has usable ETag or Last-modified headers.
1312 if (existingResource->canUseCacheValidator())
1313 return Revalidate;
1314
1315 // No, must reload.
1316 LOG(ResourceLoading, "CachedResourceLoader::determineRevalidationPolicy reloading due to missing cache validators.");
1317 logMemoryCacheResourceRequest(frame(), DiagnosticLoggingKeys::inMemoryCacheKey(), DiagnosticLoggingKeys::unusedReasonMustRevalidateNoValidatorKey());
1318 return Reload;
1319 }
1320
1321 return Use;
1322}

1390CachePolicy CachedResourceLoader::cachePolicy(CachedResource::Type type, const URL& url) const
1391{
1392 Frame* frame = this->frame();
1393 if (!frame)
1394 return CachePolicy::Verify;
1395
1396 if (type != CachedResource::Type::MainResource)
1397 return frame->loader().subresourceCachePolicy(url);
1398
1399 if (Page* page = frame->page()) {
1400 if (page->isResourceCachingDisabledByWebInspector())
1401 return CachePolicy::Reload;
1402 }
1403
1404 switch (frame->loader().loadType()) {
1405 case FrameLoadType::ReloadFromOrigin:
1406 case FrameLoadType::Reload:
1407 return CachePolicy::Reload;
1408 case FrameLoadType::Back:
1409 case FrameLoadType::Forward:
1410 case FrameLoadType::IndexedBackForward:
1411 // Do not revalidate cached main resource on back/forward navigation.
1412 return CachePolicy::HistoryBuffer;
1413 default:
1414 return CachePolicy::Verify;
1415 }
1416}

1418void CachedResourceLoader::loadDone(LoadCompletionType type, bool shouldPerformPostLoadActions)
1419{
1420 RefPtr<DocumentLoader> protectDocumentLoader(m_documentLoader);
1421 RefPtr<Document> protectDocument(m_document.get());
1422
1423 ASSERT(shouldPerformPostLoadActions || type == LoadCompletionType::Cancel);
1424
1425 if (frame())
1426 frame()->loader().loadDone(type);
1427
1428 if (shouldPerformPostLoadActions)
1429 performPostLoadActions();
1430
1431 if (!m_garbageCollectDocumentResourcesTimer.isActive())
1432 m_garbageCollectDocumentResourcesTimer.startOneShot(0_s);
1433}

1435// Garbage collecting m_documentResources is a workaround for the
1436// CachedResourceHandles on the RHS being strong references. Ideally this
1437// would be a weak map, however CachedResourceHandles perform additional
1438// bookkeeping on CachedResources, so instead pseudo-GC them -- when the
1439// reference count reaches 1, m_documentResources is the only reference, so
1440// remove it from the map.
1441void CachedResourceLoader::garbageCollectDocumentResources()
1442{
1443 LOG(ResourceLoading, "CachedResourceLoader %p garbageCollectDocumentResources", this);
1444
1445 typedef Vector<String, 10> StringVector;
1446 StringVector resourcesToDelete;
1447
1448 for (auto& resourceEntry : m_documentResources) {
1449 auto& resource = *resourceEntry.value;
1450 LOG(ResourceLoading, " cached resource %p - hasOneHandle %d", &resource, resource.hasOneHandle());
1451
1452 if (resource.hasOneHandle() && !resource.loader() && !resource.isPreloaded()) {
1453 resourcesToDelete.append(resourceEntry.key);
1454 m_resourceTimingInfo.removeResourceTiming(resource);
1455 }
1456 }
1457
1458 for (auto& resource : resourcesToDelete)
1459 m_documentResources.remove(resource);
1460}

1503ResourceErrorOr<CachedResourceHandle<CachedResource>> CachedResourceLoader::preload(CachedResource::Type type, CachedResourceRequest&& request)
1504{
1505 if (InspectorInstrumentation::willIntercept(frame(), request.resourceRequest()))
1506 return makeUnexpected(ResourceError { errorDomainWebKitInternal, 0, request.resourceRequest().url(), "Inspector intercept"_s });
1507
1508 if (request.charset().isEmpty() && (type == CachedResource::Type::Script || type == CachedResource::Type::CSSStyleSheet))
1509 request.setCharset(m_document->charset());
1510
1511 auto resource = requestResource(type, WTFMove(request), ForPreload::Yes);
1512 if (resource && (!m_preloads || !m_preloads->contains(resource.value().get()))) {
1513 auto resourceValue = resource.value();
1514 // Fonts need special treatment since just creating the resource doesn't trigger a load.
1515 if (type == CachedResource::Type::FontResource)
1516 downcast<CachedFont>(resourceValue.get())->beginLoadIfNeeded(*this);
1517 resourceValue->increasePreloadCount();
1518
1519 if (!m_preloads)
1520 m_preloads = makeUnique<ListHashSet<CachedResource*>>();
1521 m_preloads->add(resourceValue.get());
1522 }
1523 return resource;
1524}

1552void CachedResourceLoader::clearPreloads(ClearPreloadsMode mode)
1553{
1554 if (!m_preloads)
1555 return;
1556
1557 std::unique_ptr<ListHashSet<CachedResource*>> remainingLinkPreloads;
1558 for (auto* resource : *m_preloads) {
1559 ASSERT(resource);
1560 if (mode == ClearPreloadsMode::ClearSpeculativePreloads && resource->isLinkPreload()) {
1561 if (!remainingLinkPreloads)
1562 remainingLinkPreloads = makeUnique<ListHashSet<CachedResource*>>();
1563 remainingLinkPreloads->add(resource);
1564 continue;
1565 }
1566 resource->decreasePreloadCount();
1567 bool deleted = resource->deleteIfPossible();
1568 if (!deleted && resource->preloadResult() == CachedResource::PreloadResult::PreloadNotReferenced)
1569 MemoryCache::singleton().remove(*resource);
1570 }
1571 m_preloads = WTFMove(remainingLinkPreloads);
1572}

1574Vector<CachedResource*> CachedResourceLoader::visibleResourcesToPrioritize()
1575{
1576 if (!document())
1577 return { };
1578
1579 Vector<CachedResource*> toPrioritize;
1580
1581 for (auto& resource : m_documentResources.values()) {
1582 if (!is<CachedImage>(resource.get()))
1583 continue;
1584 auto& cachedImage = downcast<CachedImage>(*resource);
1585 if (!cachedImage.isLoading())
1586 continue;
1587 if (!cachedImage.url().protocolIsInHTTPFamily())
1588 continue;
1589 if (!cachedImage.loader())
1590 continue;
1591 if (!cachedImage.isVisibleInViewport(*document()))
1592 continue;
1593 toPrioritize.append(&cachedImage);
1594 }
1595
1596 return toPrioritize;
